00:35:06.147 --> 00:35:08.628
Well. I thought you
were gonna be a boy.

506
00:35:11.892 --> 00:35:13.676
Not all surprises are bad.

507
00:35:21.945 --> 00:35:23.425
Everything's gonna be fine.

508
00:35:23.469 --> 00:35:26.515
That's what Miss Farrell said.

509
00:35:26.559 --> 00:35:28.735
Well. then I guess it must be
true.

510
00:35:53.325 --> 00:35:56.197
Burt Peterson's firing
was undignified.

511
00:35:56.241 --> 00:35:58.808
Building security.
That's all I'll say.

512
00:35:58.852 --> 00:36:01.550
Confirm
a couple of rumors.

513
00:36:01.594 --> 00:36:03.596
Did he throw a desk chair
against a window

514
00:36:03.639 --> 00:36:05.293
only to have it bounce back
and knock him over?

515
00:36:06.468 --> 00:36:07.991
Not that I know of.

516
00:36:08.035 --> 00:36:10.168
Did he make a number two in
a file cabinet?

517
00:36:11.821 --> 00:36:14.868
Burt Peterson lived
hard and loved hard.

518
00:36:14.911 --> 00:36:18.045
So. Harry here is an expert in
media.

519
00:36:18.088 --> 00:36:20.265
Television. The air. not the
sets.

520
00:36:21.048 --> 00:36:23.572
Now. Admiral Television
sales are flat.

521
00:36:23.616 --> 00:36:25.183
We know that.

522
00:36:25.226 --> 00:36:26.445
But as we studied your indices.

523
00:36:26.488 --> 00:36:29.056
we realized that they're not
flat everywhere.

524
00:36:29.099 --> 00:36:33.452
In fact. among Negroes. sales
are actually growing.

525
00:36:33.495 --> 00:36:34.496
We know that. too.

526
00:36:35.410 --> 00:36:36.455
You do?

527
00:36:39.980 --> 00:36:43.462
No. of course you do.

528
00:36:43.505 --> 00:36:47.857
These are your numbers. but I think
we've discovered an interesting strategy.

529
00:36:49.511 --> 00:36:51.687
This is Ebony.

530
00:36:53.167 --> 00:36:56.562
By Negroes. for Negroes.

531
00:36:56.605 --> 00:37:02.785
Jet. Space in these magazines costs
far less than what you currently spend.

532
00:37:04.831 --> 00:37:09.314
Daily newspapers that go just to
this market for pennies on the dollar.

533
00:37:09.357 --> 00:37:10.358
And?

534
00:37:17.539 --> 00:37:19.193
Shift a portion of the media
budget

535
00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:21.195
from lower-indexing white areas

536
00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:23.284
to this market. where it
can do more good.

537
00:37:23.328 --> 00:37:26.418
They already like it and we can make
them buy more by increasing the exposure.

538
00:37:26.461 --> 00:37:29.072
A 5% sales bump in Detroit alone

539
00:37:29.116 --> 00:37:33.120
would make you the same profit
as a 2% increase system-wide.

540
00:37:33.163 --> 00:37:35.905
And ads on television geared to this
market and white markets

541
00:37:35.949 --> 00:37:37.559
will have double the effect.

542
00:37:37.603 --> 00:37:40.301
A negro ad and a white ad?

543
00:37:40.345 --> 00:37:44.087
So. Campbell. you're making
twice the ads for us now.

544
00:37:44.131 --> 00:37:47.787
No. do them together. Integrate it.

545
00:37:47.830 --> 00:37:49.223
I don't think that's legal.

546
00:37:50.572 --> 00:37:52.008
Of course it's legal.

547
00:37:52.879 --> 00:37:56.709
Look. this conversation is
not worth having.

548
00:37:56.752 --> 00:37:59.712
Who's to say that Negroes
aren't buying Admiral televisions

549
00:37:59.755 --> 00:38:02.280
because they think white
people want them?

550
00:38:08.547 --> 00:38:11.332
Miss Olson
is here to see you.

551
00:38:11.376 --> 00:38:12.420
Send her in.

552
00:38:15.902 --> 00:38:17.512
Oh. Sorry.

553
00:38:21.168 --> 00:38:24.606
I know he doesn't need
clothes. but don't return it.

554
00:38:24.650 --> 00:38:27.566
I'm the youngest. I never
had anything new.

555
00:38:27.609 --> 00:38:29.045
You didn't have to do that.

556
00:38:29.089 --> 00:38:30.612
I did.

557
00:38:30.656 --> 00:38:33.398
No one told me they were all
going in on it together.

558
00:38:36.401 --> 00:38:38.141
I heard you were back at work.

559
00:38:38.185 --> 00:38:39.665
but now I wonder if that's true.

560
00:38:39.708 --> 00:38:41.275
I invited you in.

561
00:38:43.321 --> 00:38:46.106
I don't know if this
is the best time.

562
00:38:46.149 --> 00:38:47.586
I don't know. It's kind of
serious.

563
00:38:56.334 --> 00:38:59.380
I've been thinking about my
situation here.

564
00:38:59.424 --> 00:39:01.991
and I'm so grateful to you
for all you've done.

565
00:39:03.558 --> 00:39:04.646
I just...

566
00:39:06.518 --> 00:39:09.695
Well. you know. I'm paid very
little.

567
00:39:10.870 --> 00:39:12.480
My secretary doesn't respect me

568
00:39:12.524 --> 00:39:15.701
because I make $71 more a
week than she does.

569
00:39:15.744 --> 00:39:19.531
Maybe we need to get you a
cheaper secretary.

570
00:39:19.574 --> 00:39:24.927
Paul Kinsey does the same work
that I do. and not as well sometimes.

571
00:39:24.971 --> 00:39:27.887
And I don't know if you read it in
the paper. but they passed a law

572
00:39:27.930 --> 00:39:31.760
where women who do the same work
as men will get paid the same thing.

573
00:39:31.804 --> 00:39:32.979
Equal pay.

574
00:39:35.111 --> 00:39:36.939
It's not a good time.

575
00:39:36.983 --> 00:39:39.289
It's not a good time for me.
Don.

576
00:39:39.333 --> 00:39:41.074
Do you know how
expensive this city is?

577
00:39:41.117 --> 00:39:43.990
It's not gonna happen.
Peggy. not now.

578
00:39:44.033 --> 00:39:45.818
I'm fighting for
paperclips around here.

579
00:39:57.830 --> 00:40:01.790
Third time. It must be old hat.

580
00:40:16.718 --> 00:40:18.154
You're gonna be fine. Peggy.

581
00:40:18.198 --> 00:40:19.939
I look at you and I think.

582
00:40:22.507 --> 00:40:25.118
"I want what he has."

583
00:40:25.161 --> 00:40:26.162
Really?

584
00:40:28.730 --> 00:40:34.127
You have everything.
and so much of it.

585
00:40:38.827 --> 00:40:40.960
I suppose that's probably true.

586
00:40:51.579 --> 00:40:53.451
What do you want me to say?

587
00:40:58.499 --> 00:41:00.893
I don't think I could have
been any clearer.

588
00:41:02.938 --> 00:41:05.985
You see what's been going
on here the last six months?

589
00:41:18.563 --> 00:41:20.303
What if this is my time?

590
00:41:42.195 --> 00:41:43.196
Hey.

591
00:41:45.503 --> 00:41:46.939
Where are you going?

592
00:41:46.982 --> 00:41:50.116
To the ladies room.
You want to join me?

593
00:41:50.159 --> 00:41:51.552
Did you tell Don about Duck?

594
00:41:51.596 --> 00:41:52.727
That's none of your business.

595
00:41:52.771 --> 00:41:54.729
Sure. they hear you're
shopping around.

596
00:41:54.773 --> 00:41:56.731
they'll want you more. but me?

597
00:41:56.775 --> 00:41:59.647
I'm sharing my job with Kenny.
I'm already redundant.

598
00:41:59.691 --> 00:42:01.693
You have relationships with
your clients. That's leverage.

599
00:42:01.736 --> 00:42:03.042
Did you say something?

600
00:42:03.085 --> 00:42:04.826
It's my decision. Pete.

601
00:42:04.870 --> 00:42:06.611
Your decisions affect me.

602
00:42:28.197 --> 00:42:30.243
If it isn't Martin Luther King.

603
00:42:30.286 --> 00:42:32.985
I should dropkick you off the
roof.

604
00:42:33.028 --> 00:42:38.381
Admiral Television has no interest in
becoming a colored television company.

605
00:42:38.425 --> 00:42:41.167
But they are.
It seems illogical to me

606
00:42:41.210 --> 00:42:45.780
that they would reject an
opportunity to make more money.

607
00:42:45.824 --> 00:42:47.303
Then again. I'm in advertising.

608
00:42:47.347 --> 00:42:50.742
This is a sensitive issue.
Businesses hate that.

609
00:42:50.785 --> 00:42:52.787
Let me put it in account terms.

610
00:42:52.831 --> 00:42:55.485
Are you aware of the number of
hand jobs I'm gonna have to give?

611
00:42:55.529 --> 00:42:57.575
Am I being
taken off the account?

612
00:42:57.618 --> 00:42:59.620
I'm going to have to pretend
I had you killed!

613
00:42:59.664 --> 00:43:01.622
Sales are flat.
I had to do something.

614
00:43:01.666 --> 00:43:03.624
I don't know if anyone's
ever told you that half the time

615
00:43:03.668 --> 00:43:06.627
this business comes down
to. "I don't like that guy."

616
00:43:09.151 --> 00:43:10.718
Are we done with the flogging?

617
00:43:13.678 --> 00:43:16.158
Never as good as you
think it's gonna be.

618
00:43:17.159 --> 00:43:20.815
If I may. Bert. Roger.

619
00:43:20.859 --> 00:43:24.993
it does seem as though there's
money to be made in the negro market.

620
00:43:25.037 --> 00:43:27.343
Obviously not with Admiral.

621
00:43:27.387 --> 00:43:31.521
but I don't think it would be
wrong of us to pursue it in some way.

622
00:43:31.565 --> 00:43:34.002
Really?

623
00:43:34.046 --> 00:43:39.660
I've just moved here. I'm a
stranger in a strange land.

624
00:43:39.704 --> 00:43:42.924
but I can tell you there's
definitely something going on.

625
00:43:44.665 --> 00:43:48.016
We'll look into it. You can go.

626
00:44:40.242 --> 00:44:41.722
We're here! SALLY: She's here!

627
00:44:41.766 --> 00:44:43.811
- Mommy! Daddy!
- Mommy! Mommy!

628
00:44:43.855 --> 00:44:45.160
Welcome. welcome!

629
00:44:46.771 --> 00:44:48.381
Mommy!

630
00:44:48.424 --> 00:44:50.600
Careful. Here. let me take him.

631
00:44:55.954 --> 00:44:57.477
I missed you so much.

632
00:44:59.653 --> 00:45:02.308
Wait till you see your fridge.

633
00:45:02.351 --> 00:45:06.181
If there's a power outage. you can
feed the entire street for a month.

634
00:45:08.967 --> 00:45:11.796
Hi. baby. I'm your brother.
Bobby.

635
00:45:11.839 --> 00:45:13.145
Remember. you have to be
careful.

636
00:45:14.146 --> 00:45:16.452
How was it?

637
00:45:16.496 --> 00:45:20.543
You know. It was all a fog.

638
00:45:22.023 --> 00:45:25.418
You're making a mistake not
forcing Carla to stay.

639
00:45:25.461 --> 00:45:28.813
She's been away from her family.
And I can manage.

640
00:45:28.856 --> 00:45:31.380
I know some girls.

641
00:45:31.424 --> 00:45:32.468
You want something to eat?

642
00:45:32.991 --> 00:45:34.079
Sure.

643
00:45:34.122 --> 00:45:36.124
I got it. Come on.

